=Bio=
[[File:eric_harris_braun.png|200px|thumb|left|Eric Harris-Braun]]
Eric Harris-Braun designs and builds software infrastructure for the new economy. He is a core developer of [http://ceptr.org Ceptr] and a co-founder of the [http://metacurrency.org MetaCurrency] project. He works closely with [http://ciresearchinstitute.org The Collective Intelligence Research Institute] a research and development group dedicated to understanding and developing new forms of collective intelligence, where he is the lead developer of the [http://flowplace.org Flowplace]. He is an advisory board member at the [http://www.centerforneweconomics.org Schumacher Center For New Economics], is the co-founder of [http://www.glassbead.com Glass Bead Software], a provider of peer-to-peer networking applications, and of Harris-Braun Enterprises, a free-lance software development shop, which has created, among other things, complex data-collection web-sites for the health-care industry, an Android application for catch-monitoring for the fishing industry, and which built and operates the [http://www.onlinewritingworkshop.com Online Writers Workshop]. In 1994, he published the Internet Directory, with Fawcett Columbine which sold over 100,000 copies, and which went on to a second edition in 1996 before being made obsolete by Google. Eric received a B.S. in Computer Science from Yale University. &nbsp;Currently he lives in rural New York where he is part of  a Quaker Intentional community, tends a garden and lives in a straw-bale house.
